entries.title: BuzzFeed to Use ChatGPT Creator OpenAI to Help Create Some of Its Content
entries.description: CEO Jonah Peretti said publisher would use the technology to make more comprehensive quizzes, interactive content.

entries.title: U.S. Has Disrupted 'Hive' Ransomware Group
entries.description: U.S. authorities seized the servers of the notorious ransomware group and captured keys to decrypt its software. “We hacked the hackers,” the Justice Department said..

entries.title: Tesla Stock Rallies On Optimistic Outlook From Elon Musk
entries.description: Shares in the EV maker rose more than 8% after the company struck an upbeat tone about demand and its ability to navigate a potential economic downturn.

entries.title: Renault, Nissan Near Deal on Alliance Shake-Up
entries.description: The French car maker and its Japanese partner are nearing a deal to reshape their 20-year-old alliance, in a restructuring that would reduce Renault’s shareholding in Nissan and give both companies more autonomy.

entries.title: Stripe Sets One-Year Timetable to Decide on Going Public
entries.description: The fintech startup hired Goldman Sachs and JPMorgan to advise it on a direct listing or a private-market transaction involving employees’ shares.

entries.title: Intel Expected to Post Loss as Demand for Chips Wanes
entries.description: The once-booming chip industry has been hurt by flagging consumer appetite amid worries over possible recession.

entries.title: CEO of Israeli Cyber Firm NSO Reaffirms Company Commitment to Spyware
entries.description: Yaron Shohat acknowledges past mistakes, but says the technology is vital for law-enforcement and intelligence agencies.

entries.title: Google Girds for Second Antitrust Battle as DOJ Targets Its Ads Business
entries.description: The latest lawsuit calls for the divestiture of parts of the search giant’s business.

entries.title: What the NFL Playoffs and Tech Layoffs Have in Common
entries.description: They have never had so much data to guide their decisions. But teams and companies still get hiring and firing wrong because of psychological biases.

entries.title: SAP to Cut 3,000 Jobs After Profit Plunges
entries.description: The German software company joined the ranks of tech companies announcing job cuts this year, following a 47% fall in net profit in the final quarter of 2022.

entries.title: Meta Pays BuzzFeed Millions to Generate Creator Content for Facebook and Instagram
entries.description: The partnership marks latest iteration of yearslong relationship between digital publisher and social-media giant.
